    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> This _looks_ right to me, I think this is a tricky flake to hit. Can we add a test to assert this behaviour?\r\n\r\nYeah, a test would be good.  We generate a list of say, 3 `Objecter`s --- but the middle one is a little bomb that, as a side effect to it's `RBACObject()` call, cancels the context.  Assert that we get the error back instead of a list of 2.",
